name: r-metr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.12.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-metr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/metR_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/metR/metR_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9ab084720283c51d6789eb0aeeb6661607d09ad5ebe6ccf75ba5bbf9fb2fe47f

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-formula
    - r-matrix
    - r-rcurl
    - r-checkmate
    - r-curl
    - r-data.table
    - r-digest
    - r-dplyr
    - r-fields
    - r-formula.tools
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.0.0
    - r-gridextra
    - r-gtable
    - r-lubridate
    - r-maps
    - r-maptools
    - r-memoise
    - r-plyr
    - r-scales
    - r-sp
    - r-stringr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-formula
    - r-matrix
    - r-rcurl
    - r-checkmate
    - r-curl
    - r-data.table
    - r-digest
    - r-dplyr
    - r-fields
    - r-formula.tools
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.0.0
    - r-gridextra
    - r-gtable
    - r-lubridate
    - r-maps
    - r-maptools
    - r-memoise
    - r-plyr
    - r-scales
    - r-sp
    - r-stringr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('metR')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('metR')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/eliocamp/metR
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: Many useful functions and extensions for dealing with meteorological data in the tidy data framework. Extends 'ggplot2' for better plotting of scalar and vector fields and provides commonly used analysis methods in the atmospheric sciences.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - apcamargo
    - conda-forge/r
